	(text "Load Driver High Side Switch and Relays"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 19.304 20.066 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 3.302 3.302)
				(thickness 0.6604)
				(bold yes)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "94d9e26b-c31d-4957-83a9-5dd4f9f3a165")
	)
	(text "- The load driver IC is an 8 channel high side switch, that can supply upto 500mA per channel with Vcc upto 50V.\n- The high side switch is used to power 8 relay coils, which each draw 12V 30mA (0.36W). The relays themselves are capable of\n   supplying upto 15A constant.\n- The solder bridges allow you to select from the WAGO connector output being 12V-GND, or just a connected/disconnected\n   wire.\n- For example, on the first relay, bridging SB1 and SB9 will put 12V and GND on the wago connector. On the other hand,\n   bridging SB5 alone and leaving the other two open will simply connect the loop. DO NOT CONNECT IN ANY OTHER CONFIGURATION!!!\n- Of all the high-current components, the solder bridge is the weak link. Thus, using the biggest available solder bridge\n   pad, max continuous current will be like 3 amps probably (not determined yet)\n- Because of the previous point, all fuses on this sheet will be 5A fuses."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 17.78 138.938 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "ab7f1046-4df7-4ae8-87d0-3cec26eea2d2")
	)
